<p> Additional food-safety inspectors were hired after a listerioisis outbreak in 2008 killed 23 people. </p>
<p> Fred Lum/The Globe and Mail </p>
<p> Enlarge this image </p>
<p> Public-service cuts won’t impact food safety, Agriculture Minister says </p>
<p> gloria galloway </p>
<p> OTTAWA— </p>
<p> From Tuesday's Globe and Mail </p>
<p> Published </p>
<p> Monday, Jan. 16, 2012 8:45PM EST </p>
<p> Last updated </p>
<p> Tuesday, Jan. 17, 2012 7:46AM EST </p>
<p> 76 comments </p>
<p> Email </p>
<p> Tweet </p>
<p> Print </p>
<p> / </p>
